      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 specimens from production lots; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to design drawings.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from production lots were tested. Dimensional inspection confirmed all specimens were within design tolerances. Two independent laboratories performed testing to assess inter-laboratory variability. Sample size is sufficient for the statistical comparison method (E/uval)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios; at minimum two load levels or configurations tested.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed under a single ASTM F1717 static compression-bending configuration. Only one load condition (monotonic ramp to 40 mm displacement) was applied. This falls short of the required level, which demands coverage of multiple clinically relevant conditions. This factor is below required level and is a known gap acknowledged in the assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
